technologies.name: WordPress
technologies.description: WordPress is a free and open-source content management system written in PHP and paired with a MySQL or MariaDB database. Features include a plugin architecture and a template system.

technologies.name: MySQL
technologies.description: MySQL is an open-source relational database management system.

technologies.name: PHP
technologies.description: PHP is a general-purpose scripting language used for web development.

technologies.name: Google Maps
technologies.description: Google Maps is a web mapping service. It offers satellite imagery, aerial photography, street maps, 360Â° interactive panoramic views of streets, real-time traffic conditions, and route planning for traveling by foot, car, bicycle and air, or public transportation.

technologies.name: CentOS
technologies.description: CentOS is a Linux distribution that provides a free, community-supported computing platform functionally compatible with its upstream source, Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL).

technologies.name: OpenSSL
technologies.description: OpenSSL is a software library for applications that secure communications over computer networks against eavesdropping or need to identify the party at the other end.

technologies.name: Backbone.js
technologies.description: BackboneJS is a JavaScript library that allows to develop and structure the client side applications that run in a web browser.

technologies.name: Apache HTTP Server
technologies.description: Apache is a free and open-source cross-platform web server software.

technologies.name: Underscore.js
technologies.description: Underscore.js is a JavaScript library which provides utility functions for common programming tasks. It is comparable to features provided by Prototype.js and the Ruby language, but opts for a functional programming design instead of extending object prototypes.

technologies.name: Twitter
technologies.description: Twitter is a 'microblogging' system that allows you to send and receive short posts called tweets.

technologies.name: Typekit
technologies.description: Typekit is an online service which offers a subscription library of fonts.

technologies.name: Twitter Ads
technologies.description: Twitter Ads is an advertising platform for Twitter 'microblogging' system.

technologies.name: reCAPTCHA
technologies.description: reCAPTCHA is a free service from Google that helps protect websites from spam and abuse.

technologies.name: lit-html
technologies.description: lit-html is a simple, modern, safe, small and fast HTML templating library for JavaScript.

technologies.name: lit-element
technologies.description: lit-element is a simple base class for creating web components that work in any web page with any framework. lit-element uses lit-html to render into shadow DOM, and adds API to manage properties and attributes.

technologies.name: Google Analytics
technologies.description: Google Analytics is a free web analytics service that tracks and reports website traffic.

technologies.name: Flickity
technologies.description: Flickity is a JavaScript slider library, built by David DeSandro of Metafizzy fame.

technologies.name: Google PageSpeed
technologies.description: Google PageSpeed is a family of tools designed to help websites performance optimisations.

technologies.name: Microsoft 365
technologies.description: Microsoft 365 is a line of subscription services offered by Microsoft as part of the Microsoft Office product line.

technologies.name: Open Graph
technologies.description: Open Graph is a protocol that is used to integrate any web page into the social graph.
